  <scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_1775b7355f1339eab9346d972f450de5">
    <head>Content Description</head>
<p>The collection consists of sixteen (16) photographs by Margaret Bourke-White. Subjects include the steel, oil, munitions, paper, aluminum, grain, fruit, dairy, and lumber industries, a turbine on the USS Maryland, women workers duirng WWII and astronomer Walter Adams with Mt. Wilson telescope.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <bioghist audience="internal" id="aspace_f6b22ff244594832fe50baff156e86f9">
    <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
<p>Margaret Bourke-White was born June 14, 1904, in the Bronx, New York.  She was an American photographer and documentary photographer. She graduated from Cornell University with a Bachelor of Arts degree in 1927.</p>  </bioghist>
  <relatedmaterial audience="internal" id="aspace_ba882fcce6b4e62392a8719ab776d938">
    <head>Related Materials</head>
<p>Additional Margaret Bourke-White photographs depicting Cornell University located in collection #47-1-2276, Margaret Bourke-White photographs.</p>  </relatedmaterial>
